The paper deals with two primary contributions: a novel incremental covariance update technique for SLAM and belief space planning, and an efficient approach for BSP in high-dimensional state spaces. These topics are closely related to robotics (SLAM, BSP) and artificial intelligence (BSP, covariance calculation), which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.RO and cs.AI sub-categories. The paper also involves machine learning techniques (factor graph propagation), which makes cs.LG a likely sub-category. The use of covariance matrices and information-theoretic terms suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.SY sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of trajectory parts, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.CV sub-category.
